articles.description: Jarred Vanderbilt impresses off the bench for the Wildcats dropping 11 points and picking up nine rebounds in Kentucky's 81-71 win over Collin Sexton and Alabama.
articles.headline: Kentucky holds off Alabama by 10

images.caption: Jarred Vanderbilt impresses off the bench for the Wildcats dropping 11 points and picking up nine rebounds in Kentucky's 81-71 win over Collin Sexton and Alabama.
images.name: Kentucky holds off Alabama by 10

articles.description: Tayler Persons and Ishmael El-Amin scored 18 points apiece and Ball State led the entire game to throw some cold water on red-hot Toledo, sweeping the Rockets 99-71 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Persons, El-Amin help Ball State sweep Toledo 99-71

articles.description: Jaylin Walker tossed in 27 points, sinking 7 of 12 shots from 3-point range, and Kent State pulled away late to beat Akron 78-68 on Saturday to snap a four-game losing streak.
articles.headline: Walker, Avery lead Kent State past Akron 78-68

articles.description: After attempting a rebound, Auburn forward Anfernee McLemore suffered a severe ankle injury after a bad landing and had to be helped off the court by medical personnel.
articles.headline: Auburn's Anfernee McLemore suffers ankle injury, helped off court

articles.description: Ohio State and Michigan will play a big game late in the season with Big Ten title implications at stake.
articles.headline: No. 8 Ohio State visits No. 22 Michigan

articles.description: Cassius Winston scored 17 points, and No. 2 Michigan State erased a 27-point deficit on Saturday to beat Northwestern 65-60 and extend its winning streak to 10 games.
articles.headline: No. 2 Michigan St. rallies from 27 down, beats Northwestern

images.caption: Cassius Winston gets the ball at the top of the arc and drains a cold-blooded triple as Michigan State takes a 4-point lead over Northwestern in an eventual 65-60 win.
images.name: Clutch Winston 3-pointer cements Spartan comeback
